PK — ab finally Dual Write Problem ko bhi same powerful framework me todte hain 🔥
(yeh bahut important hai system design + tumhare LMS/Kafka work ke liye)

💥 DUAL WRITE PROBLEM
🚨 1️⃣ Evolution of Pain (Nightmare Scenario)

Socho tumhari system me flow hai:

Service A → DB me write → Event publish → Service B react karega

Example:

Loan Created → DB me save → Kafka event → Notification Service
😱 Nightmare Case 1
DB write ✔️
Event publish ❌

Result:

Notification Service ko pata hi nahi

💥 System inconsistent

😱 Nightmare Case 2
DB write ❌
Event publish ✔️

Result:

Dusre services kaam start kar dete hain
But actual data exist hi nahi

💥 Ghost data / wrong state

🔥 Core Pain
2 systems:
1. Database
2. Message Broker (Kafka)

→ Dono ko sync me rakhna mushkil
🧠 2️⃣ The Cure (Concept)
💡 Problem Definition
Same operation → 2 jagah write karna
(DB + Kafka)

Aur guarantee chahiye:

✔ Both succeed
OR
✔ Both fail
❌ Why 2PC (Two Phase Commit) fails

Tum sochoge:

Use 2PC
Problem:
❌ Kafka support nahi karta properly
❌ Slow (network calls)
❌ Coordinator failure risk

👉 So 2PC = theoretical solution, practical nahi

🦸 3️⃣ Real Solutions (3 Patterns)
✅ 1. Transactional Outbox Pattern (Most Important)
💡 Idea
DB + Event → same transaction me likho
Flow
1. Begin transaction
2. Insert business data (user/loan/etc)
3. Insert event into OUTBOX table
4. Commit
Diagram
Service
   ↓
DB (User Table + Outbox Table)  ← SAME TRANSACTION
   ↓
Poller Service
   ↓
Kafka
🔥 Aha Moment
Kafka ko directly call mat karo
→ DB ko single source bana do
Problem Solved
✔ DB + Event always in sync
🧪 Trade-offs
❓ Delay
Event immediately publish nahi hota
❓ Duplicate events
Poller retry → same event multiple times

👉 Solution:

Idempotency
❓ Ordering issue
Multiple pollers → events out of order

👉 Solution:

Kafka partition key
OR Kafka Streams
🔁 2. Listen-to-Yourself Pattern
💡 Idea
Direct DB write mat karo
→ pehle event likho
Flow
1. Insert event (outbox)
2. Poller → Kafka
3. SAME service consumes event
4. Then writes to DB
🔥 Aha Moment
Event = source of truth
😵 Problem
GET request aaya → DB me data hi nahi
🛠️ Solution
Write-through cache (Redis)
🔍 3. CDC (Change Data Capture)
💡 Idea
DB logs ko read karo
→ event bana do
Flow
DB write
   ↓
DB logs (binlog)
   ↓
CDC tool (Debezium)
   ↓
Kafka
🔥 Aha Moment
Event automatically generate from DB
😵 Problems
❌ Duplicate events
❌ Ordering issues
❌ Latency (log write delay)
🧪 4️⃣ What If Sandbox
❓ Direct DB + Kafka write kare?
❌ Dual write problem
❓ Single poller rakhe?
✔ Ordering maintained
❌ Not scalable
❓ Multiple pollers rakhe?
✔ Scalable
❌ Ordering issue
❓ Idempotency ignore kare?
❌ Duplicate processing
🍔 5️⃣ Real World Analogy

Socho:

Restaurant + Delivery App
❌ Wrong way
Order likha register me
Aur separately delivery app me dala

→ mismatch possible ❌

✅ Outbox Pattern
Register me likha
+
Same register me delivery note bhi likha

Phir ek banda:

Register se uthake delivery app me daalta hai

✔ Consistent

⚙️ 6️⃣ HLD Flow (Interview Drawing)

Draw this:

Service
   ↓
DB (Main Table + Outbox Table)
   ↓
Poller / Publisher
   ↓
Kafka
   ↓
Consumers
🔥 7️⃣ Golden Interview Lines
💬 Definition
Dual write problem occurs when we try to update two systems (like DB and message broker) without atomicity, leading to inconsistent states.
💬 Solution
We solve it using patterns like Transactional Outbox, where both DB change and event are stored in the same transaction, and a separate process publishes events asynchronously.
🧠 Final Mental Model
Never do:
DB write + Kafka publish separately ❌

Always do:
Single source of truth → then async publish ✔️
💥 Ultimate Aha Moment
Consistency > immediacy